<item>
            <title>[FLINK-3255] Chaining behavior should not depend on parallelism</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3255</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, operators are chained more aggressively when the parallelism is one. That makes debugging tougher as it changes threading behavior.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The benefits are also limited: Real installations where that type of efficiency would be needed would not run in parallelism 1, or would not use a partitioning/broadcast step there (if explicitly required to run parallelism 1).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the future, when we want to allow parallelism to be adjusted dynamically, this will be even more tricky.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
